climbs.name: Under the Big Top
climbs.fa: Alec Gibbons, Don Cossel, Jim Phillips

content.description: Short Route, Bouldery crack move brings you into a thin hands slot, place gear in the roof, then use two good hand jams pods and a positive edge to jungle gym your way up and over the roof.
content.protection: Single Rack from .2-#3 BD will be more than enough for this short route
content.location: Directly behind the Carnival Crack formation in a small gully. Approximately 100 ft left of Cooper's Buttress.

content.description: Around the corner to the right of Carnival Crack is this 3" crack. Follow this an other features to the top of the formation.
content.protection: Gear to 3" Shiny bolts at the top for a top rope.
content.location: From the base of the easily spotted Carnival Crack, walk around the corner to the right and the route will come into view. Rack up here or continue to the climber's right on a trail to the top to set up your TR.

content.description:
Ascends the left most crack along the edge of Cooper's Buttress. You can jam it or get some positive liebacks- your choice! There's a thin, hollow-sounding flake about halfway up- it's solid for yarding on, but I'd place gear above or below it.

CAUTION:

I heard some buzzing in the hollow spot, but saw no bees coming or going.. just made me a little uneasy.

The bolt on the slab near the top is for the 5.8 line just to the right of this route; stay left here in the lieback crack (5.easy) and then traverse right just below the chains.
content.location: Go left around the corner from Bozo's Nose (rightmost route at Carnival Crag when facing the wall) and follow the trail 2 minutes uphill to reach Cooper's Buttress- the obvious orange blob of granite with cracks all over it. This route is the far left line.

content.description: Follow the bolts under an arching roof trending right to the diagonal left trending crack
content.location: First route on the slab at the far right side of the carnival crag

content.description: Climb the broken corner to the zig zag crack
content.location: Zig zag crack in the middle of the broken face around the corner from carnival crack

content.description: Start past a bolt then up horizontal cracks to a left trending diagonal crack.
content.location: 1 route left of the corner with one low bolt

content.description: Scramble up a short wide section (#5 optional) ending on top of a short 'pillar'. From there, move right and up over a bulge. Follow the bolt line up forgiving features to the chain anchors.
content.location: Just left of Shill's arching bolt line, look for a short wide crack topping out on a small pillar. Above a bulge to the right of the pillar you'll see a bolt line leading to the chains, in view from the ground.

content.description: Start on a slab and climb through 2 roofs/overhangs to the easier upper slab. Crux is between 2nd and 3rd bolt. Use good edges and good footwork to pull into better holds.
content.location: Uphill and right of Carnival Crack, 1st route to the right of Fun House after a shrubby break in the wall.

content.description: Climb the left side of the large block up past some bolts and slab
content.protection: gear to 2" plus a few bolts
content.location: The right side of a roof feature before the slab

content.description: Connect the cracks on the right side of the broken face
content.location: Right side of the broken face around the corner of carnival crack

content.description: Start in an obvious left facing corner and climb up and slightly right. The upper face climbs well with good protection to the short crux protected by a single bolt just under the anchors. The lower part catches a lot of dirt from above.
content.protection: 1 bolt to protect slab moves up high, most gear is <1in. aside from a 2 in. cam below crux moves. Chain anchors.
content.location: Uphill and right of Carnival Crack, begins in a large left facing dihedral.

content.description: Wide crack through some roofs to easier cracks
content.location: First bolted route around the corner of carnival crack

content.description: Route begins left of Fun House on an obvious bolted slab. Climb 5.8/9 slab moves to easy break with intermediate belay. From this large ledge pull the crux moves protected by 2 bolts then climb easier terrain to the anchors.
content.protection: 6 or 7 bolts. Gear to 1". Chain anchors.
content.location: Uphill and right of Carnival Crack.

content.description:
Follows the rightmost crack system on Cooper's Buttress until it ends, then trends a bit left with ample pro in some slightly mossy horizontals, which I cleaned out (August 2020).

No real crux, just sustained 5.7 in a sinker handcrack with great feet in or out of the crack.
content.protection: Gear to BD #2, although you could slot a #3 in places
content.location: Go left around the corner from Bozo's Nose (rightmost route at Carnival Crag when facing the wall) and follow the trail 2 minutes uphill to reach Cooper's Buttress- the obvious orange blob of granite with cracks all over it. This route is the far right line.

content.description: Grunt, cuss, bleed and scream your way up the notorious 8" crack. The crux comes in the overhanging section after a near complete rest at a ledge. After getting savage on the overhanging section, the route eases only slightly when the crack becomes vertical. It ain't over till you pull over on top and are fighting back urges to puke. Have fun.
content.protection: Gear to 8" Two shiny bolts on top to rig a top rope.
content.location: The impressive wide crack seen as you approach.

content.description: Start on the crack in the corner, then up to the slab where a bolt protects the crux
content.location: Farthest right corner on the wall right of carnival crack

content.description:
Another fun OW crack on the left side of the formation. Pretty easy to move your rope over there after trying Carnival crack.

The crux had some fun butterfly stacks.
content.protection: Bolts to TR, or a standard rack to  4-5".
content.location: If you're facing carnival crack, just go up the treacherous hill and through some vegetation to the left. Better yet, just rap in from the TR bolts.

content.description: Follow 3 bolts up then right to a diagonal left leaning crack
content.protection: Could be lead with 3 draws. Most will want to place a piece below and on top gear to 1"
content.location: Middle of the slab on the far right for carnival crag with 3 bolts
